<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-586-819  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 586 819.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  May 1 1989 v28 n9 p59(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Technical publishing tools streamline documentation process.andO;(includes related article on Department of Defense standardizationof documentation process)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Harding, Bill.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A new class of technical publishing tools called electronictechnical publishing (ETP) help streamline runaway designcomplexity in the documentation process.andP;  ETP goes beyond thebasic capabilities of a word processor or a desk top publishingsystem.andP;  For example, an ETP system automatically generates tablesof contents, lists of figures, and indexes.andP;  It also numberssections automatically with automatic renumbering followingrevisions.andP;  Today, writing documentation is a group process thatrequires group productivity tools, document management tools, andtools to insure the exacting specifications that meet contractualrequirements or regulations of the job.andP;  ETP tools help withstructure maintenance, change control, file security and accesscontrol to help manage the documentation process.andP;  ETP is still anew discipline, but it should grow rapidly.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Automated DocumentationDocument PreparationElectronic IndustryTechnical WritingIndex GenerationPaginationSystem DesignTechnologyEngineering.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartphotograph.andO;Caption:   The documentation team. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>